    main.container(role='main')
      .row.row-offcanvas.row-offcanvas-right
        .col-12.col-md-9
          p.float-right.d-md-none
            button.btn.btn-primary.btn-sm(type='button', data-toggle='offcanvas') Toggle nav
          .jumbotron
            h1= title
            p
              | This is an example to show the potential of an offcanvas layout pattern in Bootstrap. Try some responsive-range viewport sizes to see it in action.
          .row
            each book in book_list
              .col-6.col-lg-4
                h2= book.title
                p= book.summary
                p
                  a.btn.btn-secondary(href=book.url, role='button') View details »
